registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:96:      "scope": "HA5 NL-PARSE LEG ONLY, code vertical. Frozen parent eval reused byte-identically: 855 covered + 106 control (parent's 122 minus the 16-item malformed stratum, excluded by FK-NLB-5). One blind held-out NL phrasing per included query (K=1, FK-NLB-4) + 60 DEV phrasings over FRESH minted identities disjoint from every scored item (ASM-0145), authored under the design doc section-5 blind protocol, + a 60-item no-keyword synonym PROBE (descriptive only, never gated, FK-NLB-8/ASM-0144). REGISTERED HONESTY NOTE: on this vertical the mapper's lexicon leg is thin — the seven relational ops are carried by frame keywords + identifier gazetteer and the mapper's concept mapping decides only the instance-of concept slot; a5-nl therefore stresses frame+entity-linking, l3a-parse stresses lexicon mapping; each licenses only its vertical. No model, no GPU, no LLM arm, no cost claim, no head-to-head engine-vs-LLM claim.",
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:97:      "n_covered": 855,
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:140:        "ASM-0622",
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:143:        "ASM-0623",
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:147:        "ASM-0624"
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:150:      "successors": "on PASS: the NL leg may be included in any a5-llm re-freeze; on FAIL: parser-stage successor per FK-NLB-3, never more GPU (kill routing). MANDATORY FK-NLB-11 REUSE CAVEAT (ASM-0423, design doc 14.4): any successor with a MODEL-BASED arm (e.g. an a5-llm re-freeze) MUST exclude or re-phrase the 28 waived_forced_substring qids listed in data/nlb-phrasings-a5/lint-receipt.json — those items carry the answer surface inside the mandatory verbatim entity identifier (nested-definition + self-recursion semantics), which a deterministic surface-blind pipeline cannot exploit but an LLM can read the answer off the question. The lint exemption is lawful ONLY for this record's non-model arms, and the guard is FAIL-CLOSED in the pinned nlb_lint.py (design doc 14.8 item 11, ASM-0621): the DEFAULT --arms-profile model blocks green on a nonempty waived list, so a model-arm successor re-running the pinned lint is refused unless it re-phrases or excludes the waived qids; the deterministic-r0 attestation is unlawful for any record with a model arm."
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:153:      "gold-replication (measured-ceiling arm: parent's gold queries on the engine that ACTUALLY RUNS — NOT byte-identical to the parent-frozen pin, design doc 10.9 — plus the byte-identical kot_code desugar layer; must reproduce the parent-perfect 855/855 + 122/122 in-run — instrument gate G2, which IS this record's engine-continuity claim, ASM-0147)",
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:154:      "deranged-lexicon (scramble control, R0 analog of shuffled-kernel: seed-pinned fixed-point-free derangement of op->relation bindings + concept-URN targets; retained exactness must collapse < 0.10 — instrument gate G5)",
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:185:      "test": "Holm family member 2 of 2: covered mis-parse->wrong-answer rate one-sided Wilson UB vs gate 0.02 over n=855. Planning value 4/855 (UB 0.0120 at z=1.96; corrected from the draft's 0.0132 at freeze-candidate recomputation). Independent kill leg: unadjusted Wilson LB >= 0.02 is a FAIL rule (fires from 24/855; the draft's 25 was an off-by-one, corrected). WILSON_GATE DECLARATION NOTE (design doc 14.8 item 7): the gate block is declared in complement form (expected_rate 0.995, threshold 0.98) because the RT-4 constraint-9 checker powers LB-exceeds-threshold gates only; by the Wilson complement identity LB(1-p,n,z) == 1-UB(p,n,z) this is the IDENTICAL gate — the tested quantity remains the wrong-answer rate UB < 0.02 with unchanged boundaries.",
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:206:  "extrapolation_envelope_verbatim": "Measured range: R0 — no host model; ONE deterministic front-end build (mapper a1-hybrid policy sha e13dc838…, one identifier gazetteer, one frozen frame rule set), ONE blind agent-authored held-out phrasing set (K=1 per query, design-doc section-5 protocol), the parents' frozen eval/stores byte-identical, the kot_code desugar layer byte-identical to the parent pin, and the ENGINE behaviourally parent-perfect on the parent eval, re-verified IN-RUN by gate G2 (the engine sha differs from the parent-frozen pin — design doc 10.9 / 14.8 item 8, ASM-0147; no engine byte-identity is claimed), ONE 15-file Python snapshot corpus. A PASS licenses only: the closed kot-query-code/1 grammar is reachable from THESE held-out NL phrasings by a deterministic training-free front-end with <=10% covered-exactness loss and an intact fail-closed contract, on the code vertical. It licenses NO natural-user-distribution robustness claim, NO other codebase or programming language, NO other phrasing distribution, NO extraction-soundness claim w.r.t. runtime semantics (ASM-0009 unchanged), NO LLM-comparative accuracy or cost claim, NO statement about kernel usefulness to any model, and NO cross-vertical conjunction (l3a-parse licenses the family/world vertical separately). A FAIL indicts the named front-end stage and routes investment to the parser, not GPU.",
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:303:        "/analysis/n_covered",
