mock_phrasings.py 68c1e6b3ba2d7a209149a4f546853ab31e77dfc40e86802d98c6ba49265d96ad, nlb_devtune.py e7fb49314d677d5b3c9ef974b267fd68eff061609d4761069878ac23121e4a9c; mapper package kernel-mapper with a1-hybrid policy sha e13dc838… verified at import; SHARED HARNESS byte-identical with l3a-parse (FK-NLB-1); ANALYSIS PIN PROVENANCE (kot-reg/1 keeps pins.analysis_script to path/sha256/output_fields, so the provenance note lives here): analysis/a5_nl.py sha256 bcb9dfa67cb66b2df773d1986f53844f2fba7d53aa2fa5ed4834e53b58a35f47 re-pinned 2026-07-10 at the independent-skeptic round-2 RE-AUDIT remediation (design doc 14.9, ASM-0624): a5-nl stays NOT re-scoped (FK-NLB-10 is l3a-only) and keeps EXPECTED_PHRASINGS_SHA256 = eval.jsonl sha256 746b202d…; carries the round-2 fail-closed gates (G7 executable harness-pin enforcement of THIS manifest + the corpus pins on every arm body; G1 counts-integrity consuming the ASM-0480 by_family buckets as invariants: run-level covered partition over 855 + control partition over 106, family-key set equality, per-family bucket partition + exact==ok, twins, control-zero, non-negative-integer buckets — closing the reproduced exact=855/refused=855 conflict; G5 deranged-arm existence) AND the 14.9 re-audit hardening: G0 one-row-per-arm re-based on the EXECUTABLE kot-log/1 run-row supersedes channel (row identity = sha256 of the replaced log line's exact bytes incl. newline, the prev_sha256/reuse.row_hashes identity; log-append enforces at append time, G0 re-verifies independently: distinct 64-hex list typing, same-arm, non-self, no dangling, no cross-arm, no byte-duplicate rows, string config.arm required — verdict-gen passes eligible rows unchanged and the scorer is the resolution point), G1 extended with control-family acceptable sums == run-level acceptable total and strict integer typing of n_covered/n_control/dev_n/dev_parse_refused (dev_parse_refused <= dev_n), typed G2 gold counters, hardened G4 in-range division. Supersedes 4a3c7551… (round-2 pin), 18c33ed3… (round-1 phrasing-pin) and 0e8e09b9… (freeze-candidate pin)."
registry/experiments/a5-nl.json:340:      "reason": "DELIBERATE FRESH RE-RUN of the trivial-policy cells (abstain-all / answer-all, R0) that the parents' results logs already hold at mechanically indeterminate pins (producers a5, a5-llm, l3a): reuse-permission is DEFERRED programme-wide (resource-optimization-plan.md section 3 interlock, ERR_P2_REUSE_UNRATIFIED), and the logged rows could not serve as this record's arm outputs even in principle - in this record the trivial policies run over the held-out NL PHRASINGS through the pinned front-end (answer-all parses each phrasing, then fabricates deterministically where the pipeline would refuse; abstain-all refuses each PHRASING), whereas every logged parent row ran over gold STRUCTURED queries with no NL front-end in the loop; the cells are $0 deterministic CPU work re-executed fresh under this record's G0/G6/G7 gates (design doc 14.8 item 7)"
registry/schema/kot-log-1.json:4:  "title": "kot-log/1 run-record — one line in results-log/<id>.jsonl (P2 02-data-and-reporting.md section 2.2). Event-conditional requirements (run => phase/config/metrics/exit; supersede => target exit != ok; reuse => a reuse block matching a frozen kot-reg/2 reused_from declaration, ratification-gated) and the raw-metrics-only rule (section 2.4) are enforced by tools/registry/log-append.py. The reuse event (delta D9, resource-optimization-plan.md section 3 revision-1) is the RC-6 in-chain witness of consumed producer rows: {producer, producer_frozen_sha256, seqs, row_hashes}. RETRY SUPERSESSION (design-nl-boundary 14.9 item A, ASM-0624): a run row may carry `supersedes`, a list of row hashes (sha256 of the replaced line's exact bytes incl. newline — the same row identity as prev_sha256 and reuse.row_hashes); log-append enforces run-event-only, mandatory reason, targets existing exit:'ok' run rows of the SAME config.arm and phase, not already superseded (self/forward/cyclic references are structurally impossible: a target must already be a chain line). This is the ONLY lawful way to replace a successful row — event:'supersede' still refuses exit:'ok' targets, so a success can never be voided WITHOUT its replacement row in the same append.",
registry/schema/kot-log-1.json:14:    "event": { "enum": ["run", "status", "unblind", "audit-ref", "note", "supersede", "reuse"] },
