registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json:129:      "shape_recoverable_note": "FK-NLB-10 / ASM-0420 (design doc 14.2): the recoverability audit MEASURED that unmarked English cannot faithfully render the unique-maker and made-lookup shapes (0.7167 strict recovery; the 8/8 genuine shape misses fall in exactly those two families). The gated primary and S2 numerators are therefore scored over the 7 shape-recoverable IN-SCOPE families only (n_covered_scored=527), as per-family bucket sums over the score_nl by_family enrichment (ASM-0480). All 600 covered phrasings still execute; the 2 dropped families are reported descriptively in /analysis/shape_ambiguous_stratum, never gated, carved out of the envelope. Precedent FK-NLB-5 (malformed excluded as having no faithful NL rendering); here the absence of a shape-faithful rendering is MEASURED, not a priori.",
