registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json:190:      "test": "Holm family member 2 of 2: covered mis-parse->wrong-answer rate over the 527 shape-recoverable IN-SCOPE covered queries (bucket sum over score_nl by_family, FK-NLB-10 / ASM-0480 — the shape-ambiguous families' outcomes never enter this numerator, the manufactured-kill pathway design doc 14.1 preempts), one-sided Wilson UB vs gate 0.02 (the dangerous half of the fail-closed split; the safe half — mis-parse->refusal — is the primary's complement, reported by stage). Gate passes <=4/527 (UB 0.0194 at z=1.96); planning value 3/527 (UB 0.0166 at z=1.96). Independent kill leg: unadjusted Wilson LB >= 0.02 is a FAIL rule (fires from 16/527, LB 0.0203 at z=1.645). WILSON_GATE DECLARATION NOTE (design doc 14.8 item 7): the gate block is declared in complement form (expected_rate 0.995, threshold 0.98) because the RT-4 constraint-9 checker powers LB-exceeds-threshold gates only; by the Wilson complement identity LB(1-p,n,z) == 1-UB(p,n,z) this is the IDENTICAL gate — the tested quantity remains the wrong-answer rate UB < 0.02 with unchanged boundaries.",
registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json:211:  "extrapolation_envelope_verbatim": "Measured range: R0 — no host model; ONE deterministic front-end build (mapper a1-hybrid policy sha e13dc838…, one entity gazetteer, one frozen frame rule set), ONE blind agent-authored held-out phrasing set (K=1 per query, design-doc section-5 protocol), the parents' frozen eval/stores byte-identical, and the engine behaviourally parent-perfect on the parent eval, re-verified IN-RUN by gate G2 (the engine sha differs from the parent-frozen pin — design doc 10.9 / 14.8 item 8, ASM-0147; no byte-identity is claimed). A PASS licenses only: the 7-FAMILY SHAPE-RECOVERABLE SLICE of the closed kot-query/1 grammar (n=527; FK-NLB-10 / ASM-0420, design doc 14.2) is reachable from THESE held-out NL phrasings by a deterministic training-free front-end with <=10% covered-exactness loss and an intact fail-closed contract, on the family/world vertical — the gate needed for an honest NL leg in l3a-cost, inherited by l3a-cost ONLY at the same 7-family slice with the unique-maker/made-lookup exclusion restated. It licenses NOTHING about the two shape-ambiguous families (unique-maker 43, made-lookup 30): those 73 items are carried as a MEASURED partial-negative (/analysis/shape_ambiguous_stratum, descriptive only), not silence, and NO whole-closed-grammar reachability claim survives this record. It licenses NO natural-user-distribution robustness claim, NO other phrasing distribution/corpus/domain/language, NO paraphrase-set-size scaling, NO LLM-comparative accuracy or cost claim, NO statement about kernel usefulness to any model, and NO cross-vertical conjunction (a5-nl licenses the code vertical separately). A FAIL indicts the named front-end stage and licenses exactly the kill's routing: parser investment, not GPU.",
