    22	
    23	11. **RESOLVED — model-arm lint guard.** `--arms-profile` defaults to `model`, and a nonempty waiver list becomes a blocking finding ([lint](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_lint.py:281)). I reproduced the intended behavior: a5 exits nonzero/RED by default with all 28 waived qids, while explicit `deterministic-r0` is GREEN; l3a remains GREEN with an empty waiver list under either profile.
    24	
    25	## Still-open and new defects
    26	
    27	### G0’s registered supersede path cannot exist in `kot-log/1`
    28	
    29	SEVERITY: freeze-blocking
    30	
    31	Concrete mechanism: Both scorers consume a top-level `supersedes` list ([l3](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/analysis/l3a_parse.py:228), [a5](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/analysis/a5_nl.py:217)), but `kot-log/1` has `additionalProperties:false` and defines no such property ([schema](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/registry/schema/kot-log-1.json:6)). The official `event:"supersede"` mechanism cannot substitute for it: `log-append.py` permits superseding only a row whose exit is not `ok` ([log append](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/registry/log-append.py:147)), while only `exit:"ok"` rows reach the scorer ([verdict selector](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/registry/verdict-gen.py:281)).
    32	
    33	The raw G0 implementation also fails to type-check the field or constrain targets to the same arm. I constructed a dictionary-valued `supersedes` and a case where `answer-all` superseded a stale mapper row; both produced `g0_one_row_per_arm=True` and `instrument_valid=True`. Self/cycles are not explicitly detected, although because the row hash includes its own `supersedes` field, constructing one requires a SHA fixed point or collision.
    34	
    35	Why it matters: The order-dependent verdict selection is fixed, but the promised successful-retry recovery path exists only in unit-test dictionaries and cannot enter the real hash-chained log. Freezing would pin an unexecutable protocol; successful duplicate rows can only poison the experiment permanently.
    36	
    37	### The pinned NLB instrument emits an unloggable run body
    38	
    39	SEVERITY: freeze-blocking
    40	
    41	Concrete mechanism: `one_arm_body` emits a top-level `"arm"` in addition to `config.arm` ([instrument](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_instrument.py:431)); `kot-log/1` rejects that undeclared property. It also omits `event`, `exit`, and `prereg_hash`; `log-append.py` stamps several envelope fields but does not add those and then requires them for a run ([log append](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/registry/log-append.py:84), [required fields](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/registry/log-append.py:99)).
    42	
    43	Why it matters: The frozen instrument’s advertised raw output cannot be appended without an undocumented transformation that deletes and adds fields outside the pinned harness. The successful prereg dry-run validates the registry record, not this run-to-log integration.
    44	
    45	### G1 still admits contradictory and non-integral count records
    46	
    47	SEVERITY: freeze-blocking
    48	
    49	Concrete mechanism: For control families, G1 checks only that covered buckets are zero and `ok <= n`; it never requires the sum of per-family `ok` values to equal run-level `n_control_refused_acceptable` ([l3](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/analysis/l3a_parse.py:325), [a5](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/analysis/a5_nl.py:309)). Setting every control-family `ok` to zero while leaving run-level acceptable refusal at 270/106 yielded `g1_counts=True`, `instrument_valid=True`, S1 PASS, and a reported acceptable-refusal rate of 1.0 in both scorers.
    50	
    51	Additionally, `n_covered`, `n_control`, and `dev_n` are compared by numeric equality without `_count`, and `dev_parse_refused` is divided without any type or range check ([l3](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/analysis/l3a_parse.py:334), [a5](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/analysis/a5_nl.py:316)). Replacing each total with `600.0`/`855.0`, `270.0`/`106.0`, or `60.0` still produced a valid instrument; `dev_parse_refused=-1` and `0.5` also passed G4 and the whole instrument.
    52	
    53	Why it matters: A dropped control-family classification or impossible/non-integral count can still support a nominal PASS. This contradicts the claimed fail-closed “full counts integrity” and leaves round-1 finding 6 materially open.
    54	
    55	### The cited audit assumptions still contain 27/33 and 9/27
    56	
    57	SEVERITY: should-fix
    58	
    59	Concrete mechanism: ASM-0422’s rationale still says 27 existing plus 33 fresh, and ASM-0425’s live claim still says 9/27, even though both records cite those assumptions ([assumptions](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/registry/assumptions.jsonl:113)). No corrected successor assumption is cited.
    60	
    61	Why it matters: Calling these lines append-only history does not make the still-open, still-cited registered statements true. The artifact is unambiguous, so the registry should carry a mechanical superseding correction.
    62	
    63	### The pinned instrument still documents a byte-identical engine
    64	
    65	SEVERITY: should-fix
    66	
    67	Concrete mechanism: The record fields are repaired, but the pinned `nlb_instrument.py` docstring still says both mapper and gold-replication run on a “byte-identical engine” ([instrument](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_instrument.py:14)). The actual engine hash differs from the parent, as the records now correctly state.
    68	
    69	Why it matters: This is runner-facing documentation inside a pinned experiment artifact and directly contradicts the registered engine-continuity claim, even though it does not alter scoring.
    70	
    71	### The n=527 Wilson complement is not bit-identical
    72	
    73	SEVERITY: nit
    74	
    75	Concrete mechanism: Section 14.8 says the original and complement forms are “bit-equal” at 4/527 and 9/855 ([design](/home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md:1083)). At 4/527, `LB(523/527)` and `1-UB(4/527)` differ by one binary64 ULP (`−1.1102230246251565e−16`); 9/855 happens to be bit-equal.
    76	
    77	Why it matters: The mathematical identity and every integer-count gate decision are unchanged—I found zero pass/fail mismatches across all k at n=527 and n=855—but the stronger implementation-level factual claim is false.
    78	
    79	OVERALL VERDICT: defects remain.
    80	
    81	- Freeze-blocking: “G0’s registered supersede path cannot exist in `kot-log/1`”; “The pinned NLB instrument emits an unloggable run body”; “G1 still admits contradictory and non-integral count records.”
    82	- Should-fix: “The cited audit assumptions still contain 27/33 and 9/27”; “The pinned instrument still documents a byte-identical engine.”
    83	- Nit: “The n=527 Wilson complement is not bit-identical.”
