     1	#!/usr/bin/env python3
     2	"""log-append — the ONLY writer to results-log/<id>.jsonl (P2 §2, S11s).
     3	
     4	    python3 tools/registry/log-append.py --experiment <id> --agent-id runner-1 \
     5	        --record <partial.json | -> [--root <repo>] [--ts 2026-07-11T09:14:12Z]
     6	
     7	The caller supplies the record BODY (event, phase, config, metrics, cost,
     8	artifacts, exit, error, prereg_hash, ...). The tool stamps what the caller may
     9	never set: `seq` (strictly increasing from 0), `prev_sha256` (sha256 of the
    10	previous line's exact bytes, incl. its newline; genesis = 64 zeros), `ts`
    11	(UTC, unless overridden for tests), `runner` (from --agent-id), and
    12	`schema_version`. It then chain-verifies the whole existing file, validates
    13	the stamped record, and appends one canonical-JSON line.
    14	
    15	Fail-closed refusals:
    16	  ERR_P2_CHAIN            existing log fails chain verification — nothing is appended
    17	  ERR_P2_SCHEMA           record does not validate against kot-log/1, or an
    18	                          event-conditional requirement is missing
    19	  ERR_P2_NOT_FROZEN       experiment absent from registry/frozen-index.json
    20	  ERR_P2_PREREG_HASH      record's prereg_hash != frozen_sha256 in the index (G-1)
    21	  ERR_P2_DERIVED_STAT     metrics contain derived/verdict-adjacent statistics
    22	                          (p-values, effect sizes, CIs, TOST/Holm outputs, ...) — §2.4
    23	  ERR_P2_STAMPED_FIELD    caller tried to supply seq/prev_sha256/ts/runner
    24	  ERR_P2_SUPERSEDE_OK     supersede targets a successful run (exit=="ok") —
    25	                          you cannot re-roll results you don't like
    26	  ERR_P2_SUPERSEDE_RUN    a run row's `supersedes` retry channel (design doc
    27	                          design-nl-boundary 14.9 item A, ASM-0624) is
    28	                          malformed: present on a non-run event, missing a
    29	                          non-empty reason, duplicate targets, a target hash
    30	                          matching no existing log line, or a target that is
    31	                          not an exit=="ok" run row of the SAME config.arm
    32	                          and phase, or is already superseded. Row identity =
    33	                          sha256 of the replaced line's exact bytes incl.
    34	                          newline (same as prev_sha256 / reuse.row_hashes).
    35	                          Self/forward/cyclic references are structurally
    36	                          impossible: a target must already be a chain line,
    37	                          so a row would need its own SHA-256 fixed point to
    38	                          reference itself. This channel is the ONLY lawful
    39	                          replacement of a successful row — the replacement
    40	                          row lands in the SAME append that retires the old
    41	                          one, in-chain and auditor-visible (a success is
    42	                          never voided without its successor; result-shopping
    43	                          on the NLB records is additionally detectable via
    44	                          their G6 determinism gate)
    45	  ERR_P2_ACCOUNT_IN_RECORD  account-identifying material in the line bytes (RT-14)
    46	  ERR_P2_REUSE_*          event:"reuse" witness fails the D9 checks: ruling not
    47	                          maintainer-ratified (ERR_P2_REUSE_UNRATIFIED), no
    48	                          matching frozen reused_from block
    49	                          (ERR_P2_REUSE_UNDECLARED), or the witnessed seqs /
    50	                          row_hashes do not equal the re-verified producer row
    51	                          set (ERR_P2_REUSE_ROWS / ERR_P2_REUSE_PRODUCER)
    52	
    53	Minimal-spine simplification (documented): P2's status machine (refuse
    54	phase:"final" unless status is RUNNING) is reduced to "the experiment is
    55	FROZEN and the prereg hash matches" — the status-event index
    56	(registry/status.json) is not built yet. Defence in depth is unchanged:
    57	verdict-gen re-filters eligibility.
    58	
    59	Retry-supersession consumption contract (14.9 item A, ASM-0624): verdict-gen
    60	passes every eligible run row — INCLUDING a retry-superseded exit:"ok" row —
    61	to the pinned analysis script; the resolution point is the pinned scorer's
    62	gate G0, which re-verifies exactly this channel's semantics fail-closed
    63	(row-hash identity, same arm, no dangling/self targets) and scores only the
    64	surviving row per arm. This tool's append-time checks and the scorer's
    65	read-time checks are two independent enforcements of one registered rule.
    66	"""
