registry/assumptions.jsonl:45:{"id": "ASM-0042", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Back-patch rescuability at useful magnitude (planning band 0.20-0.45 of swept text-only failures) extends to SmolLM2-1.7B-Instruct on the CLUTRR covered entity slice. Basis: rescue of up to 66% of failed general 2-hop factual queries measured on substantially larger hosts; no measurement exists at 1.7B or on this slice.", "backing_ref": "arXiv:2406.12775 (2024), via reports/lit-structured-parsing-and-inner-symbolic.md section 2.2; ASM-0024 (the R1-R2 analogue, unresolved and now deprioritised)", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "B-prime itself (poc/nsk1/out/bprime/) measures the fraction directly against the amended floor; the planning band is used only to size the swept set and frame decidability, never as evidence or premise."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:47:{"id": "ASM-0044", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Adjudication-protocol operational feasibility transfers from the LLM stand-in to the human round: the blind rendering contract, position-pinned shuffle, working escape, and item decidability demonstrated end-to-end by judge-1p (preflight first-attempt pass; 360/360 items labelled, 0 no-labels; probe escape used correctly 59/60) predict that a kernel-naive human judge-1 can execute the same section-4 protocol on the same item bytes without instrument failure. Human attention span, fatigue, and labelling ergonomics are unmeasured and differ from per-item stateless API calls.", "backing_ref": "registry/verdicts/f2b-transfer-llmproxy.json /gates/adjudication_valid + /gates/probe_valid; poc/f2b-transfer/llmproxy-runs/20260710T001512Z/run-log.md; registry/assessments/f2b-transfer-llmproxy.json", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The human-judged f2b-transfer Stage-1 itself: its adjudication and probe instrument gates either hold (resolving this measured) or fire INSTRUMENT-INVALID (resolving it against). Never a premise: no schedule, budget, or design decision may rest on this entry; it exists so the operational-de-risk sentence in the llmproxy assessment carries a registered, non-load-bearing tag."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:50:{"id": "ASM-0047", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Style robustness measured on the truthstyle-2x2 pinned 3-LLM judge pool (GPT-5.6-Sol, GPT-5.5, Claude-Haiku-4.5) extends to HUMAN judges on the f2b line, in particular the pending kernel-naive human judge-1 whose Stage-1 A reading the probe cannot clear (FORK-3: any human who judges d-ts items becomes permanently ineligible as an f2b-transfer judge under LS-4, so no human is measured here). Human style/familiarity susceptibility on NSM-register text is unmeasured and may differ in either direction from the LLM pool's.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-truthstyle-2x2-f2-taxonomy.md sections 1.4 FORK-3 and 4; registry/experiments/truthstyle-2x2.json extrapolation_envelope_verbatim", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "A post-Stage-1 human style rider on FRESH items (never run before f2b-transfer Stage-1 completes, preserving LS-4 judge eligibility). Until resolved, no human-judge reading may cite truthstyle-2x2 as style clearance - the record's envelope forbids it explicitly and this entry is never a premise for any schedule, budget, or design decision."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:60:{"id": "ASM-0091", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Internal define-checkability of the self-authored onto-obo substrate (0.7710 post-8es; 0.8032 on the later foreign-filler stub tier) does NOT predict any external-benchmark kappa_B value for the define-op: the binding third leg (mapper parse of a real WiC/def-MMLU stem into the closed grammar) is untouched by this census, and the define-checkable slice is biomedical/domain-skewed (def-MMLU largely non-biomedical and WiC general-vocabulary, so yield may be small or ~0). The DIRECTION - a more mature internal substrate widens the potential external breadth surface - is named but its magnitude is unmeasured. This datum is a kappa_B breadth-SUBSTRATE readiness signal that INFORMS the efficiency-thesis breadth story but does NOT gate the feasibility verdict, whose bottom lines rest on de-confounding f2b, the NL boundary, and the g2/g3/g8/g9 semantics core.", "backing_ref": "poc/define-op-census/RUN-LOG.md; docs/design-kot-query-define-op.md SS4/SS7; docs/next/architecture-ladder.md SS10.1 (b-cov kappa_B census); docs/next/feasibility-synthesis.md SS1c/SS4", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "skeptic-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The b-cov define-lane census (architecture-ladder.md SS10.1) run over EXTERNAL WiC/def-MMLU items with gold-parse and mapper-parse counted separately - the only measurement that yields a kappa_B number - blocked on the WiC/def-MMLU data unblock (WiC 401-gated, def-MMLU unpinned) + the mapper-parse leg. Until then this entry is never a premise for any schedule, budget, verdict, or design decision."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:63:{"backing_ref": "poc/compression-census/results/b-e0-tinystories.md (dominant abstain cause unmapped-word = 2,068,450, an order of magnitude above the next cause); registry/verdicts/m0b.json (coverage 0.3542 on the friendliest measured corpus at molecules-v0)", "claim": "On a second, less-favourable corpus (instruction/QA register), B-E0 roll-up engagement would be equal or lower than the 0.592-0.643% of expanded word mass measured on TinyStories-valid - direction only, magnitude unmeasured.", "date": "2026-07-10", "id": "ASM-0102", "load_bearing": false, "owner": "designer-1", "rationale": "Mechanically grounded direction: engagement is bounded by vocabulary coverage, the dominant abstain cause is unmapped-word, and TinyStories-valid is the deliberately favourable ~1.5k-lemma m0b continuity domain - larger vocabularies mean more unmapped-word abstention. Used ONLY to explain why a second corpus is not a rescue path for idea B; NEVER a premise - the park rests on the favourable-corpus measurement alone.", "resolution_path": "Run the B-E0 census on the stipulated second corpus (stub b-e0-second-corpus); the result completes the planned two-corpus negative record and either confirms or bounds this direction reading.", "status": "open", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:69:{"id": "ASM-0112", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Direction-only mechanism reading: ANY single-position late-layer vector injected at the final prompt position at R3 on this form perturbs decoding into occasionally-correct names at a source-blind ~0.5 rate-given-change, so single-position injection probes with discrete gold-hit read-outs will remain confounded on this form regardless of source construction. The measured core (rescue-given-output-change 0.43-0.53 across all four B-prime strata; foreign-vector change rate 0.603 vs own-vector ~0.27) is MEASURED-exploratory; the generalization to other injection operators, positions, and hosts is not measured.", "backing_ref": "registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime.json analyst_recount; poc/nsk1/out/bprime/bprime_rows.jsonl sha256 f45b12e0...; the runner's flagged indicative reading in poc/nsk1/out/bprime/bprime_run.log (non-binding)", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "A redesigned probe under the ASM-0111 constraints measures this directly: if a source-keyed contrast separates real from shuffled where the naive read-out could not, the confound was the read-out (this entry resolves confirmed-as-instrument-issue); if nothing separates, the entry stays direction-only and is never a premise for any kill, schedule, or budget."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:70:{"id": "ASM-0160", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "The f2b-replicate lift (+0.1507) is kernel-CONTENT-specific - i.e. attributable to NSM semantic content beyond correct record<->item alignment (the reading the derangement control cannot support: the seed-pinned derangement destroys alignment, not NSM content, and any aligned deterministic answer table would produce the same lift and die under the same derangement).", "backing_ref": "registry/verdicts/f2b-replicate.json (shuffled recovery -0.0206, ub95 0.1076 < 0.30); registry/assessments/f2b-replicate.json does_not_license; poc/gpt56-review/SYNTHESIS.md G1; registry/corrections/f2b-replicate/3-claims-language-erratum.json L1", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "K-NULL aligned-non-NSM-store ablation (content-injection map first; frozen record knull) OR human f2b-transfer Stage-1/2. Until one reads out, forward narration says 'correct-alignment-specific' per the claims-language erratum; this wider reading is never a premise."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:71:{"id": "ASM-0161", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "The f1 byte ratio 6.7369x holds at store tiers or corpora other than lexical-wn31 at S1e5 (~1.18e5 records) - the 'store-size axis extrapolates freely (measured B/rec is size-independent)' clause of P1 SS4b row HE5.", "backing_ref": "registry/verdicts/f1.json rungs_measured=[S1e5], scale_language_licensed=none; counter-evidence at the 2,348-record haiku tier docs/design-compact-kernel-serialization-v2.md SS3.3 (~25% table+header overhead); registry/assessments/f-efficiency.json discrepancy D1 (upward-only reading); docs/research-plan/ERRATA.md E-1/E-2", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Measure the pack at the d-st store rungs (f5 inputs) or a committed small-tier corpus (stub f1-haiku-tier-ratio). Binding forward reading until then: upward-only within the same stationary corpus process; elsewhere EXTRAPOLATION."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:72:{"id": "ASM-0162", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Authoring quality (g9 composite validator-pass rate) is non-decreasing in author-model capability ('extrapolates forward monotonically with author capability', P1 SS4b row HS-A / the frozen g9 envelope). Note also: g9 as frozen is a cross-study comparison - the >=10-point margin vs DeepNSM-8B's published point substitutes for, but does not equal, a controlled head-to-head.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g9.json extrapolation_envelope_verbatim (FROZEN-but-UNRUN; clause reclassified by docs/research-plan/ERRATA.md E-3); poc/gpt56-review/SYNTHESIS.md G7 g9 row", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Repeat the g9 protocol at a second author-model rung under the same composite validator (controlled head-to-head; shares infrastructure with the N19 explication-reliability trial). Until then the clause is always cited WITH an EXTRAPOLATION tag referencing this entry and is never a premise."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:73:{"id": "ASM-0163", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "The f2b-replicate PRM-beating result (HC3; kernel-verify 0.7507 vs PRM arm 0.5267 at matched FLOPs) extends beyond the named Skywork-o1-Open-PRM-Qwen-2.5-1.5B checkpoint (math-domain process PRM, applied zero-shot, pinned revision) to trained PRMs of the 1.5B class generally, or to task-matched verifiers.", "backing_ref": "registry/verdicts/f2b-replicate.json (PRM arm 0.5267, one pinned checkpoint); poc/gpt56-review/SYNTHESIS.md G4; docs/research-plan/ERRATA.md E-4; registry/corrections/f2b-replicate/3-claims-language-erratum.json L3", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "f2b-frontier-prm successor with a frontier-scale arm AND a task-matched verifier arm whose supervision uses external gold on concept-disjoint splits (never membership-string labels, which would import the circularity the programme polices)."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:75:{"id": "ASM-0221", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Expanding the mapper's closed define-templates so they fit benchmark MCQ/cloze stems (the template-shape gap, which dominated the 0.0000 at 1,497/1,550 no-template) AND authoring definitional endorsements for the minted-but-un-endorsed CL/UBERON/PO/PATO/CHEBI shards (the endorsement-coverage gap) would raise the external define-lane kappa_B^engine above 0.0000 on the biomedical Tier-A slice. The direction is named (two distinct gaps, two named routes); the magnitude of any lift is UNMEASURED and may remain small or ~0 (def-MMLU largely non-biomedical; WiC general-vocabulary, per design memo section 4).", "backing_ref": "poc/b-cov-define-lane/census-summary.json sha 03f09f42; docs/design-kot-query-define-op.md section 4 (yield projection, ASM-0019) / section 5 (mapper templates)", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "skeptic-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Re-run poc/b-cov-define-lane/census.py after (a) the mapper template expansion (defineTemplates.ts / parseDefineQuestion) and (b) authoring definitional endorsements for CL/UBERON/PO/PATO/CHEBI; count gold-parse and mapper-parse separately, and MEASURE the delta from 0.0000. Never a premise for any downstream claim; does not gate the feasibility verdict."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:81:{"id": "ASM-0204", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing prior only: a working residual-stream content channel at mid-stack should key at roughly >= 0.8 on a two-candidate discrimination (basis: token-identity read-outs from transplanted hidden states decode at high accuracy at mid layers on larger hosts in the patchscopes family; no measurement exists at 1.7B, on this form, or under additive contrastive injection). Used ONLY to justify the 0.70 floor's headroom and the n=200 power framing; never a premise for any gate outcome or spend beyond B2P's caps.", "backing_ref": "arXiv:2401.06102 (2024) patchscopes; arXiv:2406.12775 (2024) back-patching (instrument-class precedent, via reports/lit-structured-parsing-and-inner-symbolic.md section 2.2)", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "B2P measures keyed accuracy directly at every grid cell (poc/nsk1/out/bprime2/); whatever it returns supersedes this band, which is sizing-only and load-bearing for nothing."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:96:{"backing_ref": "poc/nsk1/out/bprime2/bprime2_summary.json sha256 0ee800f7f7d1aec0aa245986aa9a27a15017ebc33d5780a9cb4104da366f76f1; poc/nsk1/out/bprime2/bprime2_rows.jsonl sha256 dadabaaea914485e387b9c1f558f5f938a7b9905159b35000957aea2a340eeba (offline gate recompute + disc-c100/breakage recounts in registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json); docs/next/nsk1-bprime2-spec.md section 5 rule 2 + interpretation boundary; run committed at b404754", "claim": "Interpretive scope rule for the B2P PASS-KEYED outcome (successor to ASM-0110 per its revisit condition): the label licenses exactly this - content-specific, item-keyed internal-write delivery is MEASURED-exploratory at R3 on the CLUTRR entity form at 2 of 9 grid cells ((lh,lt) in {(12,16),(16,16)}), under a teacher-forced paired logprob-margin read-out at alpha=1.0, n=200 swept text-only failures, beating both the arithmetic-chance coin control and the role-consistent deranged control with FWER <= 0.05. It does NOT license: free-generation rescue or any 'internal steering fixes answers' statement (the generation secondaries were pivot-fixed at a measured-dead cell, so keyed free-generation rescue at the pass cells is UNMEASURED); grounding-integration claims (per the spec's pre-fixed boundary, PASS-KEYED establishes at least echo-grade readable content delivery only, and ASM-0042 is explicitly not resolved); safety claims (the write breaks 13-16 percent of correct free generations at the keying cells even under the helpful sign at alpha=1.0); or any widening across hosts, forms, tasks, alphas below 1.0, positions, operators, or derangement seeds - each widening re-classifies the citation as EXTRAPOLATION. Every B2P row is phase:exploratory - quarantined, uncitable in a verdict, flips nothing.", "date": "2026-07-10", "id": "ASM-0340", "load_bearing": true, "owner": "designer-1", "rationale": "Fixes now what the strongest-looking exploratory positive in the line may be cited FOR before it ages into an overclaim: a 2-cell, single-host, single-seed, margin-read-out Stage-0 diagnostic. Symmetric to ASM-0110's function for the B-prime negative. Revisit condition: superseded for successor results by the Stage-1 free-generation probe's own scope rule when that probe reads out.", "status": "open", "tag": "STIPULATED"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:109:{"id": "ASM-0403", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing prior only, two legs: (a) the coin-arm content-free rescue rate at the Stage-1 keying cells is planned at roughly 0.10-0.17 (basis: rescue_real_plus 22/200 and rescue_drg_plus 33/200 measured at the DEAD pivot cell at alpha=1.0 - a different cell, extrapolated to the keying cells where no rescue measurement exists); (b) free-generation keyed steering at the keying cells is strong enough for rescue rates in the tens of percent to be reachable under the plus sign (basis: the C100 breakage sign-asymmetry, 26-28 of 100 minus-sign generations emitting the bridge name at alpha=1.0, extrapolated from correct items to failures and from the minus to the plus direction). Used ONLY for the section 5 decidability arithmetic (per-seed sign-test power approx 0.98/0.84/0.45-0.57 at true Delta 0.20/0.15/0.10, n=200; KILL per-unit probability approx 0.88-0.98 in a true-zero world) and the floor headroom; never a premise for any gate outcome, claim, or spend beyond the Stage-1 caps.", "backing_ref": "poc/nsk1/out/bprime2/bprime2_summary.json sha256 0ee800f7f7d1aec0aa245986aa9a27a15017ebc33d5780a9cb4104da366f76f1 (secondaries.keyed_emission + breakage_c100); registry/assessments/nsk1-bprime2.json analyst_recount", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Stage-1 measures rescue and control rates directly at both cells and all four alphas (poc/nsk1/out/stage1/); whatever it returns supersedes this band, which is sizing-only and load-bearing for nothing."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:116:{"id": "ASM-0425", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing/expectation note only: the l3a-parse primary planning value 0.95 is implausible - the audit sample measured natural-synonym phrasing on 9/27 = 0.333 of in-scope covered sampled items (count-maker 4/4, part-lookup 4/4, instance-true 1/4), and against the single-label mapper lexicon (no synonym table) those items are expected to abstain, putting the covered-exact rate plausibly in or below the 463-485/527 INCONCLUSIVE band (extrapolated from a 27-item audit sample to the 527-item scored set and from judge label-use to mapper parse behaviour - neither measured end-to-end). Used ONLY to set maintainer expectations that an INCONCLUSIVE/FAIL landing is live; never a premise for any gate, re-authoring, or re-design; the re-scope keeps every synonym-phrased item scored.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability.json sha256 d6365bd95e7d61a1cce7585bb446aa8f905b2b8eec08d0756a446e2e70a09bf5 (rel_synonym_only_misses); docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.3", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The l3a-parse run measures the covered-exact rate and the label-verbatim vs paraphrase stratification directly; whatever it returns supersedes this band. An INCONCLUSIVE landing re-opens FK-NLB-2 with data per ASM-0141; a FAIL routes to parser investment per the frozen kill text."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:123:{"id": "ASM-0464", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing expectations for A-E2, load-bearing for nothing: (a) the value curve is expected to concentrate in the non-English cells, because high-frequency English words are frequently already single BPE tokens (contributing ~0 by construction of value(c)) and English-centric BPE fertility is reported to run severalfold higher on non-English surfaces (direction from the design doc's explicitly-unverified memory-tagged literature note); (b) m-hat-weighting is expected to discount the high-frequency (most polysemous) strata materially, direction extrapolated from B-E0's finding that unmapped-word/mappability dominates abstention on covered English — a different estimand, English-only, magnitude unknown for A's selection strata. Used only to set expectations and to justify making m-hat-weighted reporting mandatory in A-E2; never a premise for any gate, verdict, or spend.", "backing_ref": "registry/assessments/compression-census.json (direction b: unmapped-word 2,068,450 dominant abstain cause); docs/next/io-compression-ideas.md (direction a: the memory-tagged fertility-asymmetry note, must be verified at source before any prereg leans on it)", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "A-E2 measures both terms directly on the ASM-0461-pinned tokenizers and frequency lists (per-language fertility on OUR pinned tokenizers replaces the literature claim; m-hat sampling on English cells replaces the B-E0 cross-caution); whatever it returns supersedes this band."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:125:{"id": "ASM-0500", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Interpretive scope rule for the nsk1 Stage-1 INCONCLUSIVE outcome (successor to ASM-0340 for Stage-1 results, per ASM-0340's revisit condition): the label licenses exactly this - (a) internal-write DELIVERY at echo grade is REPLICATED at R3: keyed margin accuracy 0.810/0.850 at (lh,lt)=(12,16)/(16,16) at alpha=1.0 (same point values as B2P), Wilson UB95 0.8514/0.8868 >= the 0.70 replication floor, against THREE independent Sattolo derangement seeds with all coin validity tripwires clean; (b) keying decays into the control band below alpha=1.0 (0.685/0.625 at 0.75; 0.54-0.63 at 0.5; 0.54-0.56 at 0.25) while C100 breakage co-attenuates (32-34 to 4-5 per 100) - no measured strength window separates keying from damage on this operator; (c) the echo-proof integration endpoint R- fired at ZERO of 8 units and is at-or-below the content-free coin null everywhere (mean delta vs coin -0.050 to -0.010; pooled UB95 <= 0.0384 vs the 0.10 kill bound; never beats the role control), a NET bound under ASM-0404's conservative anti-gold sign semantics; (d) the echo-confounded R+ endpoint carries a sub-floor positive residual at alpha=1.0 only (0.245/0.225 vs coin 0.125-0.240; mean delta +0.075/+0.078; not all-seeds significant at 0.00625; delta floors unmet). It does NOT license: any integration claim ('internally delivered grounding helps generation' remains UNRESOLVED - not upgraded); any integration-kill claim (not downgraded - see ASM-0501); any emission-rescue claim (R+ never fired); safety claims; or any widening across hosts, forms, tasks, operators, positions, cells, alphas, or n - each widening re-classifies the citation as EXTRAPOLATION. Every Stage-1 row is phase:exploratory - quarantined, uncitable in a verdict, flips nothing.", "backing_ref": "poc/nsk1/out/stage1/stage1_summary.json sha256 63525fcd5f67407752abeeedb0f02e31892d78ca74249f044bbb2094a5832626; poc/nsk1/out/stage1/stage1_rows.jsonl sha256 fd9f4e02baf2b1c4b9a9def9cae59a1b4cabf62c78116a4b2b32efabe3047bd7 (offline gate recompute with exact agreement in registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json); docs/next/nsk1-stage1-spec.md section 5 ordered rule + ASM-0401 floors; harness poc/modal/modal_nsk1_g2.py sha256 97f9758c2fff39e07f97ddfe74cf93cc7561807ea73b45ebd6e79b87a2833ec4", "rationale": "Fixes now what an INCONCLUSIVE that closes the flagship internal-steering arc may be cited FOR, before it ages into either an overclaim (echo-grade delivery quietly becoming 'steering works') or an over-negation (a blocked both-endpoint KILL quietly becoming 'integration is dead'). Symmetric to ASM-0340's function for the B2P positive and ASM-0110's for the B-prime negative. Revisit condition: superseded for successor results by any future internal-channel probe's own scope rule when that probe reads out.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:133:{"id": "ASM-0564", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing expectation for the compression track, load-bearing for nothing: a REAL K-A4 mappability pricing (in-context, polysemy-aware) is expected to discount the A-E2 membership band materially - plausibly enough to pull the harshest grid cells to or below the K-A2 floor, while leaving the uniform/high-fertility cells clear. Direction is extrapolated from B-E0's measured finding that mappability (unmapped-word abstention) is the binding term on covered English; magnitude is unknown for A-E2's selection strata and for every non-English cell (zero mappability evidence exists there in either direction). Used only to justify the ASM-0560 requirement that the pricing instrument precede any A-E1 selection freeze; never a premise for any gate, verdict, or spend.", "backing_ref": "registry/assessments/compression-census.json (unmapped-word 2,068,450 dominant abstain cause on covered English); registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json; ASM-0560", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The a-e2-ka4-pricing-instrument stub (registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json questions_opened): in-context m-hat sampling on a provenance-pinned corpus or a polysemy-stratified discount, at least English + one high-fertility census language; whatever it measures supersedes this band."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:136:{"id": "ASM-0522", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "g9-llmproxy severity-comparability: the proxy judge's strictness on substitutability/cross-translatability is uncalibrated to the published DeepNSM evaluation protocol, so clearing or missing the frozen +0.10 margin vs the published 0.24 point is form-preserving only; direction and size of the severity mismatch unproven; NEITHER proxy outcome bears on HS-A, the why-now argument, or authoring-cost estimates.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g9-llmproxy.json extrapolation_envelope_verbatim clause 4", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Run the human g9.review (GATE-H) on the identical 50 blinded sheets; human-composite minus proxy-composite on identical items measures the proxy severity offset directly, and the human number alone feeds the frozen g9 margin test."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:140:{"id": "ASM-0532", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "g3-llmproxy estimand gap: HS3 is a claim about human ordinary usage; LLM pass-A truth-of-claim and pass-B literal condition-satisfaction judgments approximate human judgments with unproven systematic offsets (the literalism channel can push the necessity-violation rate up via hyper-literal condition failures or down via charitable reading); neither proxy verdict direction measures the human rates.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g3-llmproxy.json extrapolation_envelope_verbatim clause 1", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Run the frozen human g3 (two independent annotators) on the identical 200 instances; per-item human-vs-proxy deltas on q1/q2 measure the offset and its direction directly."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:146:{"id": "ASM-0543", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "m0a-llmproxy agent-delta reading: per-stratum raw agreement between the blind proxy labels and the 2026-07-07 non-blind agent labels measures blindness effects and judge-family effects JOINTLY; within this design the two are unattributable, so the delta is reported-only and licenses no statement about which judge is closer to truth.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/m0a-llmproxy.json endpoint sec-agent-delta", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The human pass over the same 300 items: human-vs-proxy and human-vs-agent per-item agreement attribute the joint delta into judge-error components directly."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:150:{"id": "ASM-0552", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "llmproxy tradition-familiarity direction (shared; generalises ASM-0021 beyond the f2b line): NSM literature, NSM-style explications and reductive-paraphrase conventions are plausibly in BOTH judge vendors' training data, so proxy judges may endorse familiar STYLE rather than judge content; this plausibly inflates endorsement-type statistics (g9 composite, m0a 'correct' rates) and has unproven direction on g3's violation rates; the deranged probes bound only the crudest form in each record.", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/g9-llmproxy.json, g3-llmproxy.json, m0a-llmproxy.json extrapolation envelopes; ASM-0021", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Each human pass on identical items (g9.review sheets, g3 instances, m0a annotation sample) measures the human-vs-proxy delta directly; jointly with the f2b human round these give the familiarity channel's sign and size across four task types."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:161:{"id": "ASM-0606", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing expectation for the compression track, load-bearing for nothing: per-concept MINT cost measured on the English cached-prefix definer is expected to transfer to first order to cross-lingual definer configurations (the A-E2 fi/ja/es value cells), because per-concept cost is dominated by shared-prefix cache reads and output length rather than the target word's language; second-order risks run in both directions (higher BPE fertility of non-Latin surfaces raises the uncached suffix cost; a different lexicon/catalog changes prefix size). Unmeasured; never a premise for any gate, verdict, or spend decision.", "backing_ref": "registry/assessments/a-e2-census.json (fi/ja/es fertility concentration, MEASURED-exploratory); docs/next/io-compression-ideas.md section 2.2", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "A-E1 mint-economics pilot: include at least one non-English definitional cell once the A-F1 alignment design and a pinned non-English definer configuration exist; its measured per-concept cost supersedes this expectation."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:173:{"id": "ASM-0623", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing/expectation note only, CORRECTED-COUNT SUCCESSOR of ASM-0425 (supersede-by-citation; the ASM-0425 line stands as append-only history and is no longer cited by the l3a-parse/a5-nl records): the l3a-parse primary planning value 0.95 is implausible - the audit sample measured natural-synonym phrasing on 9/28 = 0.3214 (not 9/27 = 0.333; the in-scope covered sample has 28 items per the committed r1 artifact) of in-scope covered sampled items (count-maker 4/4, part-lookup 4/4, instance-true 1/4), and against the single-label mapper lexicon (no synonym table) those items are expected to abstain, putting the covered-exact rate plausibly in or below the 463-485/527 INCONCLUSIVE band (extrapolated from a 28-item audit sample to the 527-item scored set and from judge label-use to mapper parse behaviour - neither measured end-to-end). Used ONLY to set maintainer expectations that an INCONCLUSIVE/FAIL landing is live; never a premise for any gate, re-authoring, or re-design; the re-scope keeps every synonym-phrased item scored.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability-r1.json sha256 57e9d8d12826ae6ba28da4289fcc703109b2fb9994ef99eb589655874ea6da6d; docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 14.3 and 14.9", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The l3a-parse run measures the covered-exact rate and the label-verbatim vs paraphrase stratification directly; whatever it returns supersedes this band. An INCONCLUSIVE landing re-opens FK-NLB-2 with data per ASM-0141; a FAIL routes to parser investment per the frozen kill text."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:177:{"id": "ASM-0646", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Mechanism reading (not load-bearing for the verdict-stands ruling): the leak is a connector-attachment race — claude.ai account-level MCP servers attach to a large fraction of fresh headless -p sessions (269/818 measured) and, when a connector reaches connected state before the init event is emitted (~1% of calls), its tool definitions enter the session's tools array; --tools '' governs the built-in tool set and --setting-sources '' governs settings sources, neither of which covers account-level connectors; --strict-mcp-config structurally prevents connector attachment (mcp_servers==[] in all hardened probes), so it should suppress the race, but its residual leak rate is unmeasured at the ~1% base rate and is extrapolated, not proven — which is why the per-call init.tools==[] gate remains the binding invariant.", "backing_ref": "poc/truthstyle-2x2/mcp-tool-isolation-ruling.md sections 1 and 3; poc/truthstyle-2x2/opus-runs/20260710T182459Z", "rationale": "Separates the unproven causal story (timing race, flag effectiveness) from the measured facts (ASM-0645) and the binding protocol rule (ASM-0644), so no conclusion silently consumes the extrapolated part.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "A future large-n headless-judge pass staged with --strict-mcp-config (e.g. g9/knull-line or the next truthstyle-family run) measures the residual non-empty-init.tools rate directly; 0 leaks over >=800 calls would bound the hardened rate below the observed 1% baseline."}
